SUPERVISOR FAILURES
.BREAK
.SKIP 3
.left margin 10
I.  PURPOSE
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 18
The procedure provides orderly restoration of the Network Supervisor in 
the event of a Supervisor Failure.
.SKIP 2
.LEFT MARGIN 10
II.  DEFINITION
.SKIP 1
.LEFT MARGIN 18
Supervisor Failure.  A Supervisorr failure can be defined as, anytime a 
Supervisor leaves the Network and the standby Supervisors fails to take 
control of the Network.
.SKIP 1
.SKIP 2
.left margin 10
III.  PROCEDURE
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
When a Network Controller has determined that the Network Supervisor has
failed, they should take the following steps:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Contact (as time permits):
A.  Managerr of Network Control
B.
C.
D.  Don Murtagh 2l5-265-8170  home 2l5-265-9098
.skip 1
.indent -4
2.  Check to see if the standby terminals are logged in and operational.
If stats indicate that more than one Supervisor is active, sleep any Sup
which is:
-active, but known to be an unacceptable Sup (as specified by the shift
 supervisor);
-is high in number than any other Sup which is awake.
.skip 1
.indent -4
3.  Call Computer Operations:
Cupertino Bldg "A" - 6301         Sup5
Cupertino Bldg "C" - 7705         Sup2
Valley Forge VFO - 215-666-9660   Sup1
King of Prrussia - 215-265-8170   Sup3
Dallas DCO - 214-637-7436         Sup4

Ask them to get someone in front of the Sup machines who can see the front
of the machines and talk to you at the same time.
.skip 1
.indent -4
4.  Then ask them to positively identify the Sup's number.  Then ask them
to tell you what number is being displayed in the right most position on
the Sup's display.  The following displays are possible:
-Digit alternates between 0&1.  Sup inactive, recoverring from a crash.
-Digit alternates between 0&2 on node code side.  Sup inactive, probably
 does not have working supervisor orr Kernel software.
-Digit alternatives between 0&3.  Sup inactive, frozen, off run queve.
-Digit alternatives between 0&4.  Sup inactive and sleeping, go to 7.
-Digit alternates between 0&5.  Sup active.  Go to step 5.  
-Digit dot not alternate.  The Supervisor node ode is looping or halted.
.skip 1
.indent -4
5.  If morre than one Sup active (0&5), the Sup with the highest number
should be powered down.  Power down the Sup cope side which is displaying
AC000002.  This is accomplished by turning off the machine with the keyed
power switch located on the left side of the console.  Restore power to 
the machine after 3 minutes.
.skip 1
.indent -4
6.  Continue to monitor the Sups.
-Do nothing if you can't talk via probe to an acceptable backup Sup.  If
 there is no active Sup after 10 minutes, go to Step 7.
-Awaken an acceptable backup via the TWAKE command.  Go to Step 9.
.skip 1
.indent -4
7.  If there is still no active Sup after 10 minutes, turn the key "on" at
both engines and then simultaneously hit "INI" for the lowest numbered 
acceptable Sup.
.skip 1
.indent -4
8.  If there is no active Sup after 10 minutes, repeat the procedure in 
Step 7 on the next higher Sup number.  Repeat this procedure every l2 minutes
until you run out of Sups.  When you run out of Sups, go to the donut wheel
and buy 2 dozen donuts.  Bring them back for you fellow operations personnel
to eat while they scan the want ads for job openings.
.skip 1
.indent -4
9.  Monitor takeover.  If it looks good and you can log in, congrats!  If
it doesn't, go back to Step 8.
