CHANGE NEIGHBOR COMMAND
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.  PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure is to define the process by which the change neighbor command
is used.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  DEFINITION
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Change neighbor command - This commend enables a user to change the
indicated neighbor on a line in the nodes memory.  The Supervisor
will not make this change to its node descriptor table until a retake
occurs.
1
1
III.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The change neighbor command should only be used when a network node
cannot be taken down during a scheduled protect reconfiguration, or
if a neighbor to a dead-ended node is to be reconfigured, or upgraded
to a Tymnet II.  This commend should only be used for temporary conditions
until the actual changes can be made in the code, and the nodes are
reloaded to refect these changes.  Example:

CN  Node X  Line Y  Node Z
X = The constant node number
Y = The line number in node X
Z = The new neighbor number to which the line is to be connected.
A notation in the log book is made when this command has been issued.
Note:  The change neighbor command does not apply to Tymnet II nodes.
If the node is reloaded with the same generation of software the patch
will be lost.

