SWING SHIFT TURNOVER
.BREAK
.SKIP 3
.LEFT MARGIN 10
I.  TURN OVER - ON COMING
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
A.  TERMINALS.  Check all Sup terminals, 56KB Line monitor and consolidator
to insure that they are properly logged in.  Check Telex for any international
problems.
.skip 1
.indent -4
B.  INFORMATION.  Check the previous two shift log book entries for any
information in which swing shift will be performing for that specific
day.  The Ontyme Book must also be checked to ensure that any special
instruction(s) sent through Ontyme will be handled accordingly.  Read and
initial all previous shift entries and network control mail.
.skip 1
.indent -4
C.  Check the current status of all Ontyme, Outdialers and acct. blks.
and post to verify on the swing shift entry in the log book, on a daily
basis.
.skip 1
.indent -4
D.  Check the Day Shift turnover against all current outages, hosts,
lines and nodes to be sure that they are all properly covered.
.skip 1
.indent -4
E.  Check the shut table against the Day Shift Summary and Log book,
all shuts for which there is no explanation should be removed before
excepting turnover.
.skip 1
.indent -4
F.  Check all incomplete projects and their current statuses.  Clear all
discrepancies which can be alleviated before project implementation 
group leaves.
.skip 1
.indent 4
G.  Get any pertinent informatin concerning chronic outages, supervisor
malfunctions if any, and any other information pertaining to the
operation of the net.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  TURNOVER - OFF GOING
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
A.  Check to verify all standby sup terminals, 56KB Line Monitor and
Consolidator are all properly logged in.
.skip 1
.indent -4
B.  All telex and pertinent international abnormalities will be
annotated in the log book.  If problem not resolved, a verbal analysis
of the call will be conveyed with detailed information to both the
on-coming supervisor and pilot controller, concerning nature of problem,
all technical and maintenance groups notified, if international record
carriers (IRCS) involved know the person's name or initials last
working with you.
.skip 1
.indent -4
C.  Swing Shift Summary Report - An end of shift summary consisting of
all public network outages, nodes, hosts, one hour prior to end of
shift with last date and time of status, must be sent to (*summary)
via Ontyme.  This will also include all network shuts, dates and times
and consist discription of reason.  Report should conclude with 
identifying active supervisor and status of all other Sups, Tstat, acct. blks:
and names of all network control swing shift personnel worked that day.
.skip 1
.indent -4
D.  Outages - all public network outages nodes, hosts and line should be
on their clip board in numerical order as they appear on TMCS.  All
outages should be annotated at a minimum of two hour intervals unless
documented otherwise.  Outages with priority status will be labled as
such, and verbally expressed to both on-coming controller and supervisor
as well as documented in detail on the outage ticket.
.skip 1
.indent -4
E.  Log Book - is a reference to record all abnormal events within the
network.  Special requests, private network outages or malfunctions, all
pertinent information regarding the monitoring of the network.
